Write a function that returns the lesser of two given numbers if both numbers are even, but returns the greater if one or both numbers are odd.

Solution : 
  def lesser_of_two_evens(a,b):
    if a%2==0 and b%2==0:
        if(a<b):
            return a
        elif (b<a):
            return b
    else:
        if (a > b):
            return a
        elif (b > a):
            return b

print(lesser_of_two_evens(3,5))
